run Positive1 {
	// This is a positive instance because the only person enrolled in a course (Person1) is a Student.
	some disj Person1 : Person | some disj Course1 : Course | some disj Grade1 : Grade {
		Person = Person1
		Professor = none
		Student = Person1
		Course = Course1
		Project = none
		Grade = Grade1
		Person <: teaches = none->none
		Person <: enrolled = Person1 -> Course1
		Person <: projects = none->none
		Course <: projects = none->none
		Course <: grades = none->none->none
		Grade <: next = Grade1 -> Grade1
	}
} for 1 Person, 1 Course, 0 Project, 1 Grade expect 1

run Positive2 {
	// This is a positive instance because no one is enrolled in any course, so the requirement is vacuously true.
	some disj Person1, Person2 : Person | some disj Course1 : Course | some disj Grade1 : Grade {
		Person = Person1 + Person2
		Professor = Person1
		Student = Person2
		Course = Course1
		Project = none
		Grade = Grade1
		Person <: teaches = Person1 -> Course1
		Person <: enrolled = none->none
		Person <: projects = none->none
		Course <: projects = none->none
		Course <: grades = none->none->none
		Grade <: next = Grade1 -> Grade1
	}
} for 2 Person, 1 Course, 0 Project, 1 Grade expect 1

run Negative1 {
	// This is a negative instance because a Professor (Person1) is enrolled in a course.
	some disj Person1 : Person | some disj Course1 : Course | some disj Grade1 : Grade {
		Person = Person1
		Professor = Person1
		Student = none
		Course = Course1
		Project = none
		Grade = Grade1
		Person <: teaches = none->none
		Person <: enrolled = Person1 -> Course1
		Person <: projects = none->none
		Course <: projects = none->none
		Course <: grades = none->none->none
		Grade <: next = Grade1 -> Grade1
	}
} for 1 Person, 1 Course, 0 Project, 1 Grade expect 0

run Negative2 {
